&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;jp&quot;&gt;    
京都御所公園では、しだれ桜が注目されている。近くの大学から卒業式生が通り過ぎる。
&lt;/p&gt;</content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Kyoto" /><category term="Cherry Blossoms" /><summary type="html">At the Kyoto Imperial Palace park, a focus on a strand of weeping cherry blossoms. Graduates from a nearby university walk by in their graduation kimonos. 京都御所公園では、しだれ桜が注目されている。近くの大学から卒業式生が通り過ぎる。</summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2023/2303_DSCF7376-2.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2023/2303_DSCF7376-2.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">O River・大川</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/230317/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="O River・大川" /><published>2023-03-17T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2023-03-17T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/osaka</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/230317/">&lt;p class=&quot;en&quot;&gt;
Long exposure on the O River. Osaka&apos;s Tenjinbashi bridge lit up at night, with the Kensaki Fountain on Nakanoshima Island shooting in the air at right.
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;jp&quot;&gt;    
大川で長時間露光。夜のライトアップされた天神橋、右手には中之島公園の剣先噴水が写り込んでいる。
&lt;/p&gt;</content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Osaka" /><category term="Dusk" /><category term="Black and White" /><category term="River" /><summary type="html">Long exposure on the O River. Osaka&apos;s Tenjinbashi bridge lit up at night, with the Kensaki Fountain on Nakanoshima Island shooting in the air at right. 大川で長時間露光。夜のライトアップされた天神橋、右手には中之島公園の剣先噴水が写り込んでいる。</summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2023/2303_DSCF7328-2-mono.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2023/2303_DSCF7328-2-mono.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Sakura・桜</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/230315/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Sakura・桜" /><published>2023-03-15T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2023-03-15T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/sakura</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/230315/">&lt;p class=&quot;en&quot;&gt;
It’s the start of cherry blossom season in Kyoto. These are the Kawazu-Zakura grove along the Yodosuiro waterway in southern Kyoto, some of the earliest blooming trees.
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;jp&quot;&gt;    
京都の桜の季節が始まりましたね。これは京都南部の淀水路の河津桜で、最も早く開花する木の一つです。
&lt;/p&gt;</content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Kyoto" /><category term="Cherry Blossoms" /><summary type="html">It’s the start of cherry blossom season in Kyoto. These are the Kawazu-Zakura grove along the Yodosuiro waterway in southern Kyoto, some of the earliest blooming trees. 京都の桜の季節が始まりましたね。これは京都南部の淀水路の河津桜で、最も早く開花する木の一つです。</summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2023/2303_A7R06685-2.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2023/2303_A7R06685-2.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Kokusai Kaikan・国際会館</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/230312/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Kokusai Kaikan・国際会館" /><published>2023-03-12T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2023-03-12T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/kokusai-kaikan</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/230312/">&lt;p class=&quot;en&quot;&gt;
Kyoto International Conference Center, designed by Sachio Otani (1966), was the location of the historic 1997 &lt;a href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kyoto_Protocol&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Kyoto Protocol Treaty&lt;/a&gt; that brought climate change to international attention, committing countries to reduce greenhouse gas emissions.

&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;jp&quot;&gt;    
国立京都国際会館は、大谷幸夫の設計（1966年）で、気候変動が国際的に注目され、各国が温室効果ガスの排出を削減することを約束した歴史的な1997年の&lt;a href=&quot;https://ja.wikipedia.org/wiki/気候変動に関する国際連合枠組条約の京都議定書&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;京都議定書条約&lt;/a&gt;の締結場所である。
&lt;/p&gt;</content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Kyoto" /><category term="Architecture" /><category term="Black and White" /><summary type="html">Kyoto International Conference Center, designed by Sachio Otani (1966), was the location of the historic 1997 Kyoto Protocol Treaty that brought climate change to international attention, committing countries to reduce greenhouse gas emissions.</summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2023/2303_DSCF7291-2.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2023/2303_DSCF7291-2.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry></feed>